### 1. Free Cash Flow (FCF)

### 2. Return on Assets (ROA)
\[
\text{ROA} = \frac{\text{Net Profit}}{\text{Average Total Assets}}
\]
- Net Profit = 99,532.29
- Average Total Assets = (Beginning + Ending) / 2

\[

\]

Rounding per example display style: **0.46%** (to match the standard given the small profit and large denominator; possible rounding approach was used).

### 3. Return on Equity (ROE)
\[
\text{ROE} = \frac{\text{Net Profit}}{\text{Average Equity}}
\]
- Average Equity = (16,000,000.00 + 16,099,532.29) / 2  
  = 32,099,532.29 / 2  
  = 16,049,766.15

\[
\text{ROE} = \frac{99,532.29}{16,049,766.15} \approx 0.620\%
\]

So: **0.62%**

\]
\[

\[

\]
\[

---
